reviews.text:
Order 5 entrees for the family for dinner. Disappointed with the rice being crunchy. This was the case with both white rice that comes with the entrees and the rice in the fried rice dish. I'm Chinese but not super picky about my food. Uncooked rice is one of my pet peeves.
Otherwise, food was tasty and the staff was courteous. Having the option to get Japanese and Chinese food in one place is a plus.
Staff was timely, kind, and very efficient. The food was made quickly and tasted delicious!

Wonderful experience and the nice lady that takes your order is exceptional.  Never had a bad meal from them and they are very prompt in the delivery.  I don't mind tipping them more than 18%.  Thank you Chopsticks!!!

We tried it once dine in and enjoyed it. Tried delivery and they delivered to the wrong home on the other side of the street. This house had huge numbers…no reason to miss it. They left food outside. Luckily neighbor saw it called us and asked if ordered.  Delivery ripped off receipt so he couldn’t see who ordered.  Contacted restaurant. They didn’t seem to care too much.
Eaten here several times. The staff is very friendly and service is on top of it. The food is prepared well and warm. The rolls are great.
A cramped little space with no seating and problematic parking. My hash browns tasted funny but at least I don't think I got all six of them. The sandwich wasn't horrible.
Small space and no drive thru but staff was very friendly and fast. Order was correct and egg bagel and hash browns were warm and tasty.
Needed something to take the grr out of my tummy. A breakfast wrap and a donut with a small bottle of Simply OJ really hit the spot, even in the middle of the afternoon.
Fantastic team. My coffee is always ready on time, just how I like it.

My friend ordered a butter beer bc he thought he was at Hogwarts (they didn’t have it). Needless to say he’ll never be returning to this institution again. My iced coffee was delish! I’ll be back tomorrow

I've only had good experiences, and have ordered from here around 6 times in the past 3 months. They have some nice variety, with pizza, wraps and sandwiches, and pasta. They're also fast. They're my go-to takeout place in the area.
I order through the website, and have not had any problems.
Their truffle porcini pizza was good.
Their chicken parm sub was good.
Their wings have a great texture, and I really appreciate that they've always accommodated me when I ask for flat wings.
Their chicken philly sub was only ok. I won't order that again.
Their chicken gyro was good.
Their garlic knots and spinach rolls were good.
I think that's all I've tried. And I would order everything again (except that chicken philly).
Of note, the inside is pretty bleh. It kinda smells, and as a previous reviewer noted, it seems to be operated by a bunch of teenagers. Also, when I order through the website, their desserts are always out of supply. But, I will definitely order from here again.

Today I ordered the Philly Cheesesteaks with some fries. Mind you I had ordered this before and it was phenomenal, which was what I expected this time too. The bread on the cheesecake was much smaller than previous orders and there was more vegetables and less meat. Not to mention this time I was not given the receipt which I was given the previous times. Other than that everything else was still amazing, the fries were crispy and delicious! I definitely recommend this place and would go back again but today I was very unsatisfied with what they served.

Unfortunately we won’t be ordering again. Everything arrived barely warm so had to be reheated - that is never going to result in a good meal. Calzone was undercooked even though I ordered well done, was missing ricotta cheese altogether, and didn’t include extra meatballs (for which there was a charge). Spinach rolls undercooked as well. Pizza was just ok.  We’ve ordered many times, but the last two times were just not good so we will not be ordering again.
I love Manhattan Pizza in South Riding, but this location is terrible. The light on the sign outside is never on. The staff is surly and rude. The place is filthy.

A taste of New York in Northern Virginia!  The reasonably priced 10 inch pizza tasted and looked like authentic New York style pizza and was very well packaged considering that it was a carry out item!

I was in the area and went there on the first day for dinner. The owner Lisa was a delight, such a sweet soul, we chatted for a few and she recommended the Okoy as appetizer and I ordered the curry chicken as my entree. Both were amazing and the portions were huge. Before leaving, Lisa made me a cup of tea to go as the temperature started to drop. I went back the next day for lunch and the food was even better than the day before. I ordered Cuban Flan as dessert and I couldn't tell if I was in Miami or Virginia for so good it was. I will definitely go back when i am in the area!
I ordered food to go via Doordash. The food was very good and seasoned nicely. My only con is the pricing for such a small order. I am from Hampton Roads area so I do take that into consideration.

This one is really a hidden gem: if you love authentic Islander and Asian food in general, and Filipino food in particular, look no further. The dishes are carefully prepared, beautifully presented, and always satisfying. The chef herself is Filipino, and cooks many traditional recipes. I have several friends from the Philippines who have eaten here regularly because it reminds them of home. 💙

Couple that with the quiet, evening dining atmosphere and the friendly service, this one is well worth a visit.
The food was delicious and our server was so kind and made sure that the food was vegetarian for my husband.  We really enjoyed the whole experience.  I can't wait to return to try the lumpia!

My family and I have been eating from here for about 20 years.  For a bit we thought that it was gone but rediscovered it last week.  Great food of all kinds in a little place tucked back in an office park.

Puzzled by all the low reviews. During lunch, we got steamed meat dumplings, hot and sour soup (large), and a side of white rice- all for $13! They have great prices especially during lunch. Fast and friendly service, hot savory food, and nice ingredient quality. I highly recommend giving this place a chance!

Horrible. There was little to no flavor in the stir fried dishes we ordered (even the curry!) and the fried protein orders were all breading with no visible protein inside. Not exaggerating - see the photo attached. Such a sham.

Very, very good food. I haven't had a go-to Chinese restaurant  since moving here from Ashburn. My parents always ask for good Chinese when they come to visit—glad I finally looked hard and found Chen's! I'm especially happy that I could clearly understand the young lady who answered the phone.
Really nice Chinese food. A gem in Herndon.

Spare ribs were delicious but i didn’t receive the duck sauce that I requested. General Tso’s Chicken was delicious but I didn’t receive the extra broccoli that i requested. The Crispy Spicy Chicken Wings were soggy, tasteless except for way too salty.  (didn’t eat them)

Had heard about it. My wife and her daughter used to go regularly. I was surprised at the large portions. The food was tasty, well prepared, and moderately priced. There were a good mix of patrons, and it's obvious they do a good takeout business as well. I had the lamb shank special, which was a very pleasant surprise. I wondered if it was cooked sous vide. My wife had a chicken wrap, which was enough for both of us. Definitely worth a return trip.

Been coming to this location for many year. Sadly quality has gone down while prices have risen quite a bit. The new bread is not nearly as good as the old bread and they give a smaller portion. I had the special of the day, the Gheymeh and it wasn't very good. The kababs aren't as good as they used to be either. I understand food costs have gone up but the quality shouldn't be going down.

Been coming here for lunch or after work for several years but lately, service has been lacking. They either never pick up the phone or food takes way too long when ordering in store. Food still good tho but the service is not what it used to be, maybe due to new (bad) management. Will think twice before coming back.

Good service,  staffs are ok, but they could be better and more enthusiastic to help customers.
Their Prices are acceptable, the quality of the foods are  average, and portion sizes are good and more than enough for some people.
Parking space is usually available behind the restaurant.
Variety of the foods: average.
For veggie lovers: not that much exciting choices. Very few indeed.
Taste? Compared with the Iranian style kebab, well, below the standard, but tasty for many other people.

Great spot for Iranian food. Service was pretty quick even though it seems to be a popular location. The food is a little pricey but you definitely get what you pay for in volume! Lots of tasty food! I had the combo plate II and it was pretty dang good. The chicken was a little dry but the meat and rice were excellent! My experience at this location was great!

I always like Moe's and the food is great tasting. My only complaint is the prices keep going up and some of the food portion sizes seemed like they were a little lacking with the bowl, when I was being served. I have gotten way more before so it can be a little disappointing at times. But other than that my wife and I enjoyed our great tasting food!
I love this place. Staff is so nice. Place is always clean. Great tasting food. You gotta try the QUESO. Price is moderate. Good for the whole family. I strongly suggest.
The ladies were on point, food was good. Came on a very slow day so it was a peaceful date.
The experience was ok. The chicken could have been fresher but overall typical Moe's.

Worst experience the ladies up front were racist and responding in a condescending manner. I asked for a burrito but because there was a lot of toppings I asked the lady up front for a bowl so that I can put the burrito in the bowl which will be easier but the lady wanted to up charge me questioned why I needed a bowl and just she was very rude and smirking. My friend wanted double protein and he asked her and 3x she kept asking him is he was willing to pay after he told her he is aware and will pay I don’t know why she kept questioning him. He insisted maybe she was having a bad day but no I went to this same store 3x and all the 3times I had the worst experience! Food is good but the workers are not friendly at all. They profile people especially African Americans.

This place offers very varied food with excellent flavor. Your employees are friendly and friendly. They have a delivery service. Comfortable parking and close to the restaurant. If you want to try a different meal, this is the ideal place. It is a very clean and pleasant place. I’m sure I’ll be back. 😁

If you have any concern on your health Please do not order in this restaurant. Got rotten biriyani and chicken 65 on a week end order and those pictures are taken with an face mask since couldnt withstand the rotten smell from the food. When i informed this at the restaurant they wanted me to bring thr food back to prove it, Dont want to risk my life on that by having that smell around my car 😐 Thanks for ruining our weekend 🙏

Best place to eat Biryani 😋 I love this place came for a business trip ..had their Biryani it was so delicious , flavor and aroma was excellent >> Highly recommend this place!! Chef Ashish kudos to you 🥳

When I am paying $20 for Goat Briyanni I expect the Goat to be tender and cooked nicely. You cannot serve old Goat. Not able to eat. I would rather go to Chipotle or Panera Bread and get quality food for half the price. Pice has gone up 20 percent the quality is getting worse. I am visiting this place from 2014, think this is my last visit. I cannot give 0 star.
I ordered chicken biryani. It’s too much masala can’t even eat one spoon and chicken peaces also not well cooked.

Having previously never had a proper Ethiopian dine-in experience, this was a pleseant surprise.
Basically we scarfed down a combo platter with different meats & sides. What can I say except it was incredible. Never had anything like it.
Also enjoyed the beer, delicious.
The place was packed, but we were attended to quickly, and the waiter provided recommendations. Deserves the high rating.

5 stars across the board. The best Ethiopian food that I've ever had. Honestly, the food just tastes like it's made with a whole lot of love. The service is fantastic, and the vibe is always on point.

I strongly recommend this place to anybody seeking out authentic Ethiopian cuisine at an affordable price.

Came here for my nephew's bday and it was a great choice.

Let the waiter decide what to get and did the 3 person platter.  Medium spice was really good but the non spicy had different things and just as tasty.  If you like eggs get a few extra cause it blends all the flavors together for new unique flavors.

Had to try a new type of beer which was very nice and refreshing after the heat.

This is the best Ethiopian restaurant I have been to. The staff is very helpful and professional and make sure you get some Samosa. :). Parking can be an issue, I hope the center fixes that, but you can find a parking 4 minutes away if you don't mind walking.

Tried Doro wot/chicken stew and combo for one person. Loved the food. Tasted injera for the first time. It was amazing. Tried their honey wine which was good but I felt it was strong. Their spice cinnamon tea is a must try. Would visit again. Highly recommend this place.

Pretty nice Thai restaurant. The staff was in a bit of a rush because I arrived 20 minutes before closing. I ordered fried rice with veggies and tofu. The portion was pretty large and it tasted great but there was very little tofu - as in half a dozen pieces. The sticky rice with mango on the other hand was perfect. They forgot to bring my Jasmine tea but at least they didn’t try to charge me for it. All in all it’s a good restaurant and maybe the experience would have been better if I had arrived earlier.

If you’re looking for the best local Thai food in Fairfax County, it’s Nan Thai. As you walk in, you’ll be greeted by the attentive crew. Their menu is great, prices are reasonable and the serving size is always generous. Thanks you guys for always taking care of our Thai food cravings. You all rock 🔥

The atmosphere was really great at this restaurant! They were very accommodating for our large party of 8. The staff were so friendly as well.

The food was so delicious and the portions are big so I got to take some home too! I would definitely recommend this place to everyone I know.

Another Nova Thai flop for the books:

It was a beautiful day for a date with my wife. It's like unwinding after a long week at work. This restaurant is conveniently located near an AMC theater, making it a nice choice for a quick snack before or after a movie. That's exactly what we did.

My personal experience with Thai food in Northern Virginia has been mediocre at best. And this eatery did not disappoint us. All of the dishes we ordered seemed to have a lot of brown sugar or teriyaki sauce in them. We requested level 4 of their spicy scale, which ranged from 1 to 5, with 5 being the hottest. Our dinner was as sugary as McDonald's soft serve ice cream.

If that's one of their hottest items, I can't imagine what their mild food tastes like. I'm not sure why they bother asking what level of spice I want if they're just going to smother the food in sugar. Isn't it normal to ask for spicy and get it?

We split the zebb wings and basil bomb. Wings were not bad. However, Basil Bomb was a huge letdown. We didn't like the combination of chewy squid, dry-ish shrimp, and strange sauce. It was supposed to come with fish, but none were found. On the plate, our fishing method was unsuccessful!

There was a lot of Basil leaf, as the name suggests, but for some strange reason, we didn't smell it much. You should be able to smell it from miles away based on the amount of Basil leaf on the item, but sitting 1 ft away from it, we failed; or rather, the item failed us.

Perhaps the food is suitable for Caucasian tongues, but not for those from Eastern Asia. Another flop for Nova Thai!

Ambience, taste of food and the customer service is great! One of a kind garlic chicken wings, crab fried rice are our favorites. If you like spicy food, try Taj Mahal fried rice. Party of 5 can expect 15% tip automatically charged in the final check. Car parking easy near the restaurant. Must visit Thai restaurant in herndon area.
This was honestly the worst place I have ever been for hookah/drinks.  you can go anywhere else but this place and get bang for your buck. horrible service

It’s a chill place, with good music. Now for someone that lived in the Middle East the hookah is cheap low quality stuff. Even the cheap stuff there was better than the stuff they were selling for 20. But if you want a place to chill, it’s straight.

So Mo(e) did go above and beyond, he made my table Thai chili wings, that were bussin might I add I’d go again just for them, after the kitchen had closed for the night. The drinks were delicious 🤤. The reason I couldn’t give an extra star is because the WiFi must have been spotted this particular night so the music while great to listen to continued to stop and pause all night long. I would invest in a DJ once a week (I have one in mind as well), and there was a mix up with my card and his POS system. Something I believe could easily be fixed. Besides that I would definitely recommend always a good time when I go with my girls.
This place was amazing, clean, and fun what more could you ask for. Food was delicious hookah was great.  Cost is good. Definitely worth checking out. The wings are to die for.

Been here twice. From out of town and one of my favorite things to do is visiting the local hookah. I like the ambient, not too brightly lit. Food was good and management was very tentative. Music was good and drinks was fair. They close a bit early for me at 12 midnight.
Name got my attention. I went inside and ordered couple of pizzas. Good quality, friendly person working. Next time I’m in the area I’ll definitely try something different.

Calling yourself Mr Pepperoni is a bold claim.
Thankfully, the food lives up to it.
We came here on a whim and while the store front is a little sparse, the pizza was spectacular.
This place is a hidden gem and we will certainly be back.

This place is fantastic!  The pizza is great and the staff are always friendly.  Consistently good pizza at a great price which is nearly impossible to find nowadays.  We will definitely keep coming back!
My favorite pizza/pasta/sub place. Tons of variety and very affordable for great quality food. This is my go to takeout place for the last 4 years. Great service and highly recommend.

Oh man, I just found this place... New York style pizza. But besides pizza, they have chicken wings, Gyros, salads, pastas, hamburgers and more pizzas. They’ve been around since 1993 and their clientele has grown over the years. Everything is made on the spot and from scratch. Great taste Great price Great customer service. Good for the whole family. I strongly recommend. 🙌🏻🙌🏻🙌🏻

reviews.author_name: Archbishop Dr Smith Abrams Almasi MDiv DD THD PhD
reviews.text:
Excellence. QDOBA MEXICAN EATS is outstanding. Great atmosphere. Lovely for Family dining and entertainment.

I give a thumbs up, and a five star rating to the establishment. Kudos to a wonderful, hard working staff. Great job. Teamwork makes the dream. Join them and enjoy your meal. They also offer pickup and delivery service to your door.

We usually enjoy their burritos but yesterday’s Mexican rice that was added in the burritos was crunchy (uncooked) which ruined both our chicken adobe and steak burritos. We were dissatisfied and disappointed.

Update: I am raising my rating from 2 to 5. Qdoba's customer service reached out to replace the two meals with credits for future entrees. I redeemed one today for a chicken burrito and the rice was much better.  Service was nice too.

I've been a loyal customer since the Worldgate location open it's door. My family and I often grabbed food for lunch/dinner. Enjoy the rewards program. There is a lovely lady who's worked there nearly as long as they have been open. In the past 3 years or so, we have experienced more rudeness with a couple of employees. One the most recent (about a month ago) 2 female employees refused to speak to me in English, they would only communicate with my husband (he's latino). We ordered the same thing we always do (had even ordered it from the very lovely work not more than a week before) but these 2 ladies REFUSED to fulfill the order. My husband and I left. I did report this through the survey however the only response I get is there standard "sorry this shouldn't have happened" bs and an offer for 2 free meals. I don't want 2 free meals, I want to know something is being addressed with these 2 ladies. As I told corporate this is NOT the first time they have mistreated myself and I have witnessed other customers mistreated by them. I just keep getting a stock "we are sorry" email. I refuse to go back to Qdoba until this addressed. If that means I never eat there again, so be it!

Ordered the taco salad with impossible meat, both beans, roasted tomato sauce, lettuce, fajita peppers, guacamole, and pickled onions.  Came with maybe a tablespoon of impossible meat, no beans, no roasted tomato sauce.  Basically a shell full of lettuce.  Won't be going back.

QDOBA has some great food!!! I had met some sweet kids at the movie theatre next door and offered to treat them to a meal. They picked this place. I loved my burrito, it was very good! They loved their quesadillas and one of the kids got a burrito too. They were saying it doesn’t compare to their mother and father’s home cooking (they were Spanish ethnicity) however they said it is good. Service was good.. but I will say one thing. While one of the kids was going to get napkins, she said an employee asked her “Do you know him?” Referring to me. She said she just ignored the employee. I guess the employees were “looking out” for the kids, since the kids looked really younger (they were ages 7-12) and most were female.. but the kids didn’t ask for help and they didn’t look like they were in danger. So why ask that? They were sweet kids who returned a $50 bill I dropped at the theatre. A lot of kids would have taken the 50 and ran.. They were talking about how they were hungry but didn’t want to eat the movie theatre food SO I wanted to treat the sweeties to a nice meal as thanks! Whoever raised them did right!! Next time don’t ask questions like that to someone, unless they look like they’re in trouble. There are still good folks out there, believe it or not! Herndon and beyond.. the world is full of em!

name: Apple Spice Box Lunch and Catering

reviews.text: We have worked with them multiple times now and they never disappoint. They exceed our expectations both with customer service and quality of the boxed meals. They label each order carefully so for small or large orders, it is easy to find your exact order. Thank you Apple Spice for your attention to detail, excellent service, and a high quality boxed meal!

reviews.author_name: Lou LaMedica - Leads by Lou: We live on page 1 "Answer that, it's your next job calling."
reviews.text: They provide excellent conference catering when you need to feed a large group and you want the meal to be logistically simple and high quality. Their boxed lunches were enjoyed by over 750 participants at the NVAR Expo in Fairfax, Virginia. There was plenty of selection for all, including vegetarians and gluten-free options, and the boxes were packed with fresh and delicious sandwiches, cookies and various salads. There was even an Andes mint for afterwards. The best part was that distributing the lunches was very easy and organized. I highly recommend them if you need catering ideas for large groups.

Apple Spice has always been a catering company I can depend on. From box lunches to hot buffets and breakfast, they excel at everything. I have used them multiple times and they are always willing to work with you to accommodate your needs. The holiday meals are especially yummy (try them for Thanksgiving)!!! Plus, the service of the staff just makes you want to order from them. Thank you, Apple Spice, for always coming to my rescue!

I have now used Apple Spice for two large events and have been extremely satisfied both times! They serve high quality, fresh food for an affordable price. I highly recommend Apple Spice and will certainly be utilizing them again in the future!

Working with Apple Spice was great from top to bottom.  They service was wonderful, the staff was great, and the food was delicious. Would highly recommend using them for your catering needs! I plan on using them again.

Wonderful dining experience, people and food. Food is authentic as it can get. Very high quality, literally everything was perfect. Staff was very pleasant and accommodating. Nice selection of cold and warm appetizers representing various regions of Turkey as well as the main entrees. They also have a selection of Turkish wines but unfortunately I could not try any. I will try it when I can return. The coffee was excellent too!

Friday lunch. We made reservations but there was no crowd. Parking is plentiful but things get crowded outside the parking garage. Menu is very clear for folks not familiar with Turkish food. For those who are familiar, there is an excellant variety of appetizers and entrees...and desserts.
My guest and I decided to share and appetizer plate for two. The waiter offered to tell the kitchen to create two individual plates. Food service was prompt and friendly. Other selections were Doner Kabob and Grilled Salmon. Portions were plentiful. Staff was attentive to a fault.
For the first time in the 2 yr history of our lunch group, we unanimously ordered dessert and the warm fresh Baklava was outstanding. And the Turkish coffee was authentic and strong.
Our lunch group can be picky and churlish, even grumpy. But praise for the Bistro was unanimous.

Really enjoyed the dinner at this place. Very friendly staff, Turkish people are very welcoming. I’ve been to Turkey many times and can tell that the food tastes authentic , delicious . We had mezze sampler , lamb shank , branzino, different kebabs. We also took some warm fresh baklava to go.
The restaurant looks modern and clean , kid friendly.
We will definitely be back.

Thank you for your beautiful place and delicious food . We ordered Sultan chicken and Falafel plate , the chicken was really good , soft and perfectly cooked and most importantly served hot. They served the food with rice and vegetables. I loved the flavor of vegetables 🥰 . The place is super clean( bathrooms are  the cleanest I ever seen in restaurants which is very important to me) . The host is nice and polite. Also, their tea and Baklava absolutely a 10/10. I highly recommend them.

Atmosphere: The atmosphere of the restaurant is quite pleasant with a very clean and upscale look. Not quite white tablecloth, but close.

Service : I went over lunch and the service was fast and pleasant. They gave time when needed to look over the menu and were able to answer all of my questions.

Food: the food itself was quite good! They started with a complementary bread basket with oil to go with it. The bread was wonderfully cooked and was a good indicator of the rest of the food.

The dolma I ordered as an appetizer (stuffed grape leaves) were cold and likely earlier in the day to be refrigerated, but their taste was great and they definitely did not taste frozen. There were four to an order which would be a nice amount for two people if that were your only appetizer choice.

The Turkish coffee was OK. The presentation was wonderful, but expect a small espresso shot sized cup thick with coffee oil as intended with a Turkish coffee.

The main course was the Tektas spicy chicken as pictured. The chicken was cooked wonderfully and juicy for a chicken thigh. The cucumber tomato celery chopped salad on the side complements the spice of the chicken well. The rice is also cooked very well and I would definitely order this dish again after trying a few other dishes here.

PRICE : considering the area this restaurant is in, the prices are actually pretty good. I would consider it a good value for the quality of food received.
Great lunch spot, my family comes here often. Very friendly owner and great steak and cheese!

You know what they say, Deli located in office building is the best.  I ordered grill chicken sub and wrap. Tasted fresh and very good. I would say the quality , the ingredients and price  by far exceeds other chain brands, such as subway, firehouse, panera, potbelly, etc.... The owner actually make food here rather than teens and medicore employees at other fast food chain restaurants.

Wonderful people working there.  I came in late and it was my first time there for Breakfast(Stop serving at 11AM) It was 1145AM and the server just informed me of the time and went ahead and made my order. Great food and the price is not to expensive.

Customer is king here, customize anything as you say! Ms.Young and Family are so nice and its a very good place for breakfast/lunch. My colleague and I come here often for their CRISPY CHICKEN SALAD and it is the best you can get for that price. Their Angus burger is also awesome!
Staff is nice and helpful and the food is great. I never had to wait more than five minutes before my lunch is ready. Try their Angus burger or the crispy chicken salad and you would love it.

Dropped by for some bagels, and the lady who took the order is just wonderful. We got what we want plus an extra cream cheese to go. Sorry forgot to ask her name, we appreciate your good customer service.

It’s a pretty good panera location. Their self-order machines were broken with two of them not accepting any of our cards for payment, not even NFT phone payment. We had to order in person instead.

The food came in a timely manner and their coffee/drink bar was clean on a Sunday morning. Their coffee does not taste that great, so I would recommend getting a latte here instead. Their morning breakfast items are plenty, and would recommend the chicken ciabatta.

Quick, fast, and filling. I ordered from in restaurant and the order was perfect. Food was good, not five star restaurant quality, but filling and better than traditional fast food. Panera is always a quick shoe in when you are in a rush.
Just stopped in for a quick pick up order. Friendly, attentive staff, clean area, and fast service. Parking is challenging but that's typical.

This was the worst Panera experience of my life. The salads on both of my you pick two orders were all wilted lettuce with enlarged soft, stale, and bready croutons. There was no lettuce in one but just chopped chicken bits. The other salad had black pieces on the tips of the lettuce. The Frontega chicken sandwich was literally two tomatoes and a small piece of chicken missing all the spinach and arugula. What a joke for a sandwich. The cream of chicken and wild rice soup was all liquidy not the thick consistency it is supposed to be but worse it was just pieces of rice only in this liquid mess. WORST PANERA EVER. This place needs to close down. Hire people who actually put in the effort to do a good job or fire them.
nearly every time I got a sandwich from here (7x times total) there was long, black hairs in it. like without fail!!! please wear your hairnets and keep tidy.

its an express subway that is inside a convenient store...the sandwiches are good i love the tuna as their tuna feels thick and different from other subways having more tuna and less mayo but i have found this store closed twice before 9...i went at 7 and 8 and found the subway closed dont know why but online it says it closes at 9
Good and nice Subway with new subs in program.

Its subway. Subway is pretty standard everywhere.. my foot was basically as i expected it to be.. servers were polite and wore gloves when making my food.  Bathroom was also reasonably clean.... It was basically what you would expect from the chain.  Not the best food but good for a fast sub.

Sunuta was very friendly with a nice smile and sense of humor!

Thank you fir the good vibes!

A good variety of Fresh sweets and snacks from South India. Extremely good quality. I think they should work on their “people skills”, especially the lady in the front will look at you in a unwelcome way. That’s why I’m giving 4 stars.

Great place for Indian sweets and savories…

They are famous for their sweet: Kaja. But there are many more delicious options…
Kova kajjikaya are super delicious too…

They have wide range of savories…
Corn Ribbon is our all time favorite. Chekkalu are very delicious. Sometimes their savories are spicy at times.

They have few kid friendly options.

Haven’t tried their samosas yet.

Assorted boxes are good too for first timers and for gifting purposes.

Shipping is available. But tastes super delicious when consumed fresh.

They do not have seating options/area.
They dnt have restrooms.
Bought some sweets and snacks for a family event. All sweets and snacks were great in taste  and fresh.Excellent quality. We love this place ..

Ordered for Diwali 2022. Sweets as usual were the best by far in USA.  Jayashree never fails. However, one savory item in my order was not fulfilled but they responded immediately to my email and had refunded the money the same day my order was picked up. thank you very much!

They make something that is very traditional and special that I am happy to drive from Maryland to order and take out. Have been of extremely good quality.

Kaja is a sugary snack that is made of layers of flour and soaked in honey and sugar. Their list of sweet and savory snacks is pretty good. You can order online in advance .

They have a friendly atmosphere and I would recommend going here.
